          "username": "mgkwill"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-07 10:15:09.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(3 comments)\n\n> hello, Marcus,\n > for the CreateVcpeResCustService.groovy file, there are so many\n > change about the space/tab etc. which makes the code hard to\n > review.\n > is it possible to avoid this like only submit the code change? :)\n\nHi Libo, Thanks for the review. I understand your concerns and depending on project process, I agree. Only minor changes to CreateVcpeResCustService.groovy are present. But a lot of formatting changes make it difficult to see what's changed. I've highlighted them with comments. \n\nWhile working on CreateVcpeResCustService.groovy it was apparent and annoying that the file did not live up to code conventions (java granted, but in large part groovy code should be extended to java).\n\nPlease see my comments for changes outside of formatting. \n\nEach project has preferences for patches, committers and PTLs create the culture for patches. It seemed to me from listening to Seshu in calls that he prefers patches that fix all issues with a file rather than small succinct code changes specific to a single issue.\n\nIf that is not the case I'm happy to amend, but please review the change as such until Seshu or other committers disagree.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
